 Glengrey - Police in Glengrey are requesting assistance from the community to find a missing 36-year-old man Asanda 'Pillay' Noveve, who went missing from his home at Zwartwater Administrative Area on 09 May 2019. "It is alleged that he was staying with his grandparents and just left home without informing them," described police spokesperson, Captain Namhla Mdleleni. "He never went back. "He was last seen wearing red short pants and white golf shirt." She said that anyone, who can shed light on his disappearance can contact Warrant Officer Xakeka 079 896 9489 or 047 878 0050. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 